 isn't too good so it is normally up for grabs.<P>The Fright Forged Shield from Paineel isn't too hard and gives off a wacky yellow light.  Kind of unnerving the first time you put it on, but the stats are very nice.  You should do those quests.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Mirriana_00</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hmmm.  Log on.  Get into group.  Tilt camera towards floor so I'm not distracted by spell/bard effects and commence with the healing.  VI could limit my view to 10' in all directions and I'd be 99% as effective.<P>It is nice when walking through that tunnel from TT to the swamp.  Probably not many in the game who know that place like a human cleric.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Bodin</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">GSB on this human cleric 24 x 7</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Alle</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I have the Crown of Hatred that casts UV.  It comes from the second floor in Hate.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Chaldaea</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I wear the GSB while traveling and switch it out with the Velium diamond ring while grouped.<P>I never leave home without my GSB.<P>------------------<BR>Chaldaea DeBebylon - Samsara</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">ElMoMo</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">GSB when I need it, Imbued Plat Diamond ring the rest of the time.<P><P>------------------<BR>Elmomo Warhound - Paragons of Fury -- The Nameless<BR>58th Ray of light of Mithaniel Marr<BR>Personal Physician to Princess Misling Tick`Atok, keeper of the ochre cup of T'Gger, rogue of my heart.<P>--Life sucks at full mana--</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aerie</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Fright Forged Helm - 11 AC, +2 str, -5 cha, +4 wis. Human and Erudite cleric only. No drop. The effect is IV and see invis wrapped into one, and I believe it's a permanent effect. (no need to right click) Result of a <A HREF="http://"http://gameznet.com/eq/quest/pavatarfright.html"" TARGET=_blank>Paineel quest</A>.<P>Edit: I forgot to answer the question.  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/tongue.gif"> No, I can't think of an item that gives UV that's obtainable by a group of level 50s. (unless you have a pet magician) Personally, the only time I really notice the difference between UV and IV is in those Kunark outdoor zones with poor lighting.<p>[This message has been edited by Aerie (edited 06-07-2001).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aquinas</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">  <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>I wear the GSB while traveling and switch it out with the Velium diamond ring while grouped.<HR></BLOCKQUOTE><BR>Exactly what I do.  I've never run into a situation where infravision wasn't sufficient to get around.<P> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>It is nice when walking through that tunnel from TT to the swamp. Probably not many in the game who know that place like a human cleric.<HR></BLOCKQUOTE><BR>Hehe, that is so true.  Until I got the GSB, I usually ended up navigating that tunnel like a submarine, just looking at the my map and my /loc coordinates.<p>[This message has been edited by Aquinas (edited 06-07-2001).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">JanSorensen</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">The crown from 2nd floor in Hate is to my knowledge the only option.<P>Mikar<BR>High Priest of Brell<BR>The Companions<BR>The